Peru Stocks: Aceros Arequipa, Edegel, Siderperu, Volcan Rise

-- B y   N a t h a n   G i l l
-- 
2011-06-08T20:48:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-08/peru-stocks-aceros-arequipa-alturas-minerals-siderperu-rise.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:30 p.m. New York time.  The  Lima  General Index jumped 3.5 percent to 20,581.13. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index rose 3.1 percent to 2,585.75.  Mining, metal and energy companies rose for a second day,
leading gains in Lima, after President-elect Ollanta Humala said
in an interview with  CNN  en Espanol last night he may ask
central bank President Julio Velarde to stay in his post,
offsetting investors’ concerns he plans to scrap policies that
led to the region’s fastest economic growth.  Edegel SAA (EDEGELC1)  (EDEGELC1 PE), the Peruvian unit of  Spain ’s
Endesa SA, soared 11 percent to 1.96 soles.  Minera IRL Ltd. (MIRL) 
, a U.K. minerals explorer with a gold mine in Peru,
rose 6.4 percent to $1.17. Steelmaker  Empresa Siderurgica del
Peru SAA (SIDERC1)  (SIDERC1 PE), a unit of Gerdau SA known as Siderperu,
gained 6.1 percent to 1.40 soles. Volcan Cia. Minera SAA
(VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s largest zinc producer, advanced 5.6
percent to 3.04 soles. Corp. Aceros Arequipa SA (CORAREI1 PE),
the Lima-based steelmaker, climbed 5.4 percent to 2.73 soles.  Peru is the world’s biggest silver producer, and third in
copper and zinc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nathan Gill in Quito at 
 ngill4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  